<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900822-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>900822-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Aura Systems Inc.:   Firm to Produce Actuators   For Big U.S. Auto Maker</HL><DATE>08/22/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AURA</CO><LP>   Aura Systems Inc. said it has entered into a contractvalued at roughly $34 million with one of Detroit's Big Threeto provide electromagnetic actuators for automobiles.   An actuator is a device that takes an electrical input andthen generates a force that can move a part. Aura Systemsdeclined to say precisely what its actuators will be usedfor, but said the components will be incorporated intosix-cylinder cars.</LP><TEXT>   &quot;They will have a special application at first, but thenthey will become standard at a later point,&quot; Harry Kurtzman,Aura's president, said in an interview. &quot;The details shouldall come out in the next few months.&quot;   Mr. Kurtzman said that the auto maker asked not to benamed at this time.   Pre-production development and testing is scheduled tobegin immediately, Aura Systems said, with initial productionof about 1.7 million units scheduled to start in summer 1991.That batch of units, priced at about $20 apiece, will takeabout a year to build.</TEXT></DOC>